		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blogs.ewebpedia.com/?p=769</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<p><p>Feed on <a href="http://blogs.ewebpedia.com/how-to-transfer-pictures-from-iphone-to-computer/">How to transfer pictures from iPhone to computer | Automatically</a> by <a href="http://blogs.ewebpedia.com">::EwebpediA BloG::</a></p><p>So, you are new to iOS or iPhone and captured a bunch of high quality snapshots through it. It looks and feels really great to have an iPhone and contents inside it. Especially ,if we are passionate about digital photography, high end devices like iPhone is our best companion. But, if one is not tech [...]</p></p><p>Copyright © <a href="http://blogs.ewebpedia.com">::EwebpediA BloG::</a> </p>]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Feed on <a href="http://blogs.ewebpedia.com/how-to-transfer-pictures-from-iphone-to-computer/">How to transfer pictures from iPhone to computer | Automatically</a> by <a href="http://blogs.ewebpedia.com">::EwebpediA BloG::</a></p><h1><a target="_blank" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/trevainsworth/" rel="" style="" target="" title=""><div id="attachment_776" class="wp-caption alignleft" style="width: 94px"><img style="" src="http://blogs.ewebpedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/iphone-pc-150x150.jpg" alt="how to transfer pictures from iPhone to Computer" title="iphone-pc" class="size-thumbnail wp-image-776  wp-caption alignleft wp-caption alignleft wp-caption alignleft wp-caption alignleft wp-caption alignleft wp-caption alignleft" height="84" width="84" /><p class="wp-caption-text">Ewebpedia &copy;-- Photo Courtesy by trevainsworth</p></div></a></h1>
<p>So, you are new to iOS or iPhone and captured a bunch of high quality snapshots through it. It looks and feels really great to have an iPhone and contents inside it. Especially ,if we are passionate about digital photography, high end devices like iPhone is our best companion. But, if one is not tech savvy or a newbie to use iPhone, it is definitely a challenge for them. So (putting them in my mind), in this tutorial, we are going to discuss on <strong>how to transfer pictures from iPhone to computer</strong> of PC having WindowsOperating System especially, Windows 7.</p>
<h1><span style="font-size: 14px;">How to Transfer Pictures from iPhone To Computer </span><span style="font-size:14px;">|</span><span style="font-size:14px;"> Apparatus Required:</span></h1>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-size:12px;">iPhone 3G/3Gs/4/4S ( latest firmware is recommended )</span></li>
<li><span style="font-size:12px;">iPhone Data Cable</span></li>
<li><span style="font-size:12px;">Personal Computer having Windows Operating System 7</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span id="more-769"></span></p>
<h2><span style="font-size: 14px;">Automatic Procedure:</span></h2>
<p>In windows 7, most of the functions are user friendly, so the computer itself will asks or suggests the user on many operations. So, when the autoplay feature is enabled in<a href="http://blogs.ewebpedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/gjivans-iphone.jpg" rel="" style="" target="_blank" title=""><div id="attachment_772" class="wp-caption alignleft" style="width: 160px"><img style="width: 151px; height: 172px;" src="http://blogs.ewebpedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/gjivans-iphone-150x150.jpg" alt="how to transfer pictures from iphone to computer" title="gjivan's iphone" class="size-thumbnail wp-image-772  wp-caption alignleft" height="150" width="150" /><p class="wp-caption-text">Ewebpedia &copy;</p></div></a> windows, a pop-up window will automatically appear in the desktop screen when iPhone is connected to the computer which is definitely a very easy task. From that pop-up window, you can perform various tasks like</p>
<ul>
<li>You can import pictures and videos.<br />
<hr />
<p>&nbsp;</p>
</li>
<li>You can import media files.<br />
<hr />
<p>&nbsp;</p>
</li>
<li>You can even open the device explorer<br />
<hr />
<p>&nbsp;</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p>So, this process is definitely automatic as it is performed in just one click. But, if the autoplay feature is turned off or inactive, this process does not work. For this, you have to follow the manual process which is mentioned below.</p>
<h2><span style="font-size:14px;">Manual Process:</span></h2>
<p>As like the method mentioned above, this is also similar, but this is not going to happen in one click.</p>
<p><a href="http://blogs.ewebpedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/portable-device.jpg" rel="" style="" target="_blank" title=""><div id="attachment_775" class="wp-caption alignleft" style="width: 160px"><img style="" src="http://blogs.ewebpedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/portable-device-150x150.jpg" alt="how to transfer pictures from iPhone to Computer" title="portable device" class="size-thumbnail wp-image-775  wp-caption alignleft wp-caption alignleft" height="150" width="150" /><p class="wp-caption-text">Ewebpedia &copy;</p></div></a>1) Connect your iPhone to your computer with data cable. ( If the iPhone is connected for the first time, windows will update its driver )</p>
<hr />
<p>2) Click on Windows Start button then Computer or My Computer. ( Shortcut to open My computer or Windows Explorer is Windows key+ E in keyboard ).</p>
<hr />
<p>3) There you can see Portable Devices under which your iPhone will be displayed. ( If you&#39;ve specified any name of your iPhone, that will be displayed).</p>
<hr />
<p>4) Right click on your iPhone and there you can see <em>&quot;Import Pictures and Videos&quot;</em>, just click it. Or you can enter inside the iPhone and choose pictures you want to transfer. Then you can copy and paste to your desired location at your computer.</p>
<hr />
<p>So, these are the easy methods on<strong> how to transfer pictures or videos from iPhone to Computer</strong>. If you have any other method or process, please pour them in comments.</p>
