			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Feed on <a href="http://blogs.ewebpedia.com/dementia-treatment/">Dementia Treatment and Care</a> by <a href="http://blogs.ewebpedia.com">::EwebpediA BloG::</a></p><p>Dementia in simple and understandable language is &quot;losing mind&quot;. This actually is not a disease but is the symptom which can be the earlier onset of Alzheimers. Please have a look on the <u><strong><a href="http://blogs.ewebpedia.com/difference-between-alzheimers-and-dementia/" target="_blank" title="Know the Difference between Alzeimers and Dementia"><span style="color:#b22222;">difference between alzheimers and dementia.</span></a></strong></u> We can feel the pain of people having dementia. They lost their cognitive abilities like memory, retention, understandings, problem solving, judgment etc. There are various types of dementia but, in this post i am going to focus only in <strong>dementia treatment</strong> and care assuming, you have a clear picture about the types already. But, before moving ahead, you need to know that, causes of dementia is divided into two types i.e. reversible and irreversible. In the later cause, brain cells in both the cortical and sub-cortical areas are damaged and this is probably due to Alzheimers or Parkinson&#39;s disease. When the cause of dementia is irreversible, the motive of treatment should be to make life of the patient as well as caregiver easy. Below, i am going to highlight some points for <strong>dementia treatment</strong> which is reversible.</p>
<p><span id="more-666"></span></p>
<h1><div id="attachment_673" class="wp-caption alignleft" style="width: 160px"><img style="" src="http://blogs.ewebpedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/dementia-150x150.jpg" alt="dementia treatment" title="dementia" class="size-thumbnail wp-image-673  wp-caption alignleft wp-caption alignleft wp-caption alignleft wp-caption alignleft wp-caption alignleft" height="150" width="150" /><p class="wp-caption-text">Ewebpedia Network &copy;</p></div><strong><span style="font-size:16px;">Dementia Treatment: Tips</span></strong></h1>
<ol>
<li>
<p>As dementia is the decrease in cognitive functioning of brain, the patient can be involved in memory trainings, cognitive practices programs. Being a membership of <u><strong><a href="http://blogs.ewebpedia.com/dementia-support-groups/" target="_blank" title="More about Dementia Support Groups"><span style="color: rgb(178, 34, 34);">dementia support groups</span></a></strong></u> is another best option.</p>
<hr />
<p>&nbsp;</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Can be given vitamin B12 in case of vitamin deficiency.</p>
<hr />
<p>&nbsp;</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Analysis of thyroid hormone&nbsp; is necessary, and after that, thyroid hormone can be supplied in case of hypothyroidism.</p>
<hr />
<p>&nbsp;</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In case of depression, patients can be given antidepressants.</p>
<hr />
<p>&nbsp;</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Involve in concentration training like meditation, yoga.</p>
<hr />
<p>&nbsp;</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Medications to ease anxiety, agitation and hallucinations can be taken</p>
<hr />
<p>&nbsp;</p>
</li>
</ol>
<h2><span style="font-size:14px;"><u>Dementia Treatment by Occupational Therapy:</u></span></h2>
<p><div id="attachment_674" class="wp-caption alignleft" style="width: 160px"><img style="" src="http://blogs.ewebpedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/dementia-treatment-150x150.jpg" alt="dementia treatment" title="old age dementia" class="size-thumbnail wp-image-674  wp-caption alignleft wp-caption alignleft wp-caption alignleft" height="150" width="150" /><p class="wp-caption-text">Ewebpedia Network &copy; -- Photo by Julian Mason</p></div>Apart of medications and drug treatment, non-pharmacological treatment may also have similar or better results. And, Occupational Therapy is one of them. This therapy can also be used along with medical prescriptions by doctor. Occupational Therapy mainly focuses on engaging the patient in some occupation and making busy. Like scheduling simple home works, gardening etc.</p>
<p>As the growth in dementia, the patient will generally lose his/her sense and routine habits. They tend to forget small happenings of their surroundings. In this case, occupational therapy can be a best option to make them involve in some work as well as train their brain in some aspect. Apart of the treatments involved, the most important thing to remember for every caregiver, especially family is to always deliver love and care.</p>
<p>[ P.S. The tips mentioned above for <strong><em>dementia treatment</em></strong> and care are based on various research and surveys, but before taking any kind of medications, please consult your registered medical pracitioner ]</p>
